  "prompt": "When will the iPhone 6s be launched?",
  "response": "The **iPhone 6s** was officially launched by Apple on **September 25, 2015**. Here's a brief overview of its release timeline:\n\n- **Announcement:** Apple unveiled the iPhone 6s and iPhone 6s Plus on **September 9, 2015**, during an event at the **Steve Jobs Theater** in Cupertino, California.\n  \n- **Availability:** Pre-orders for the iPhone 6s began shortly after the announcement, and the devices became available in stores worldwide on **September 25, 2015**.\n\nThe iPhone 6s introduced several new features at the time, including **3D Touch**, an improved **12-megapixel rear camera**, **Live Photos**, and the **A9 chip**, which offered significant performance enhancements over its predecessors.\n\nIf you're interested in current iPhone models or have questions about newer releases, feel free to ask!",
